aches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["String"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a string `s` consisting of digits.\n\nReturn `true` if the **absolute difference** between every pair of **adjacent** digits is at most 2, otherwise return `false`.\n\nThe absolute difference between `a` and `b` is defined as `abs(a - b)`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** s = \"132\"\n\n**Output:** true\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- The absolute difference between digits at `s[0]` and `s[1]` is `abs(1 - 3) = 2`.\n\n- The absolute difference between digits at `s[1]` and `s[2]` is `abs(3 - 2) = 1`.\n\n- Since both differences are at most 2, the answer is true.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** s = \"129\"\n\n**Output:** false\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- The absolute difference between digits at `s[0]` and `s[1]` is `abs(1 - 2) = 1`.\n\n- The absolute difference between digits at `s[1]` and `s[2]` is `abs(2 - 9) = 7`, which is greater than 2.\n\n- Therefore, the answer is false.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= s.length <= 100`\n\n- `s` consists only of digits.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["String"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a string `s` consisting of digits.\n\nReturn `true` if the **absolute difference** between every pair of **adjacent** digits is at most 2, otherwise return `false`.\n\nThe absolute difference between `a` and `b` is defined as `abs(a - b)`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** s = \"132\"\n\n**Output:** true\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- The absolute difference between digits at `s[0]` and `s[1]` is `abs(1 - 3) = 2`.\n\n- The absolute difference between digits at `s[1]` and `s[2]` is `abs(3 - 2) = 1`.\n\n- Since both differences are at most 2, the answer is true.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** s = \"129\"\n\n**Output:** false\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- The absolute difference between digits at `s[0]` and `s[1]` is `abs(1 - 2) = 1`.\n\n- The abs