itive number by `k`, use the **floor** value of the division result.\n\n- When dividing a negative number by `k`, use the **ceiling** value of the division result.\n\nReturn the **maximum** possible sum of a **non-empty** subarray in the resulting array.\n\nNote that the subarray chosen for the operation and the subarray chosen for the sum may be **different**.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [1,-2,3,4,-5], k = 2\n\n**Output:** 14\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Multiply each number in the subarray `[3, 4]` by 2.\n\n- This results in `nums = [1, -2, 6, 8, -5]`.\n\n- The subarray with the largest sum is `[6, 8]`, so the output is `6 + 8 = 14`.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [-5,-4,-3], k = 2\n\n**Output:** -1\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Divide each number in the subarray `[-3]` by 2.\n\n- This results in `nums = [-5, -4, -1]`.\n\n- The subarray with the largest sum is `[-1]`, so the output is -1.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `-10⁵ <= nums[i] <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= k <= 10⁵`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-subarray-sum-after-multiplier/","problemName":"Maximum Subarray Sum After Multiplier","problemNumber":3976,"problemSlug":"maximum-subarray-sum-after-multiplier","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":3976,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":4582464,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3977-minimum-time-to-reach-target-with-limited-power/3977-g1.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/3977-g1.png","sha256":"26d926d78d97935fd376cbcbece295580b85e856e0a07cadf8e7927ece9c58b1"},{"assetIndex":1,"bytes":4834632,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3977-minimum-time-to-reach-target-with-limited-power/3977-g22.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/3977-g22.png","sha256":"063ac6e213750bb75b3f72c0ed045f4f6c2f7fad9507b1d5fcd0ae27945a631b"},{"assetIndex":2,"bytes":4885393,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3977-minimum-ti