e `k = 1`, every pair is valid.\n\n- The maximum value is obtained from a pair `(0, 2)`, which is `nums[0] + nums[2] = 5 + 9 = 14`.\n\n- Thus, the answer is 14.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= n == nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `1 <= k <= n - 1`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Medium","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given an integer array `nums` of length `n` and an integer `k`.\n\nA pair of indices `(i, j)` is called **valid** if:\n\n- `0 <= i < j < n`\n\n- `j - i >= k`\n\nReturn the **maximum** value of `nums[i] + nums[j]` among all valid pairs.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [1,3,5,2,8], k = 2\n\n**Output:** 13\n\n**Explanation:**\n\nThe valid pairs are:\n\n- `(0, 2)`: `nums[0] + nums[2] = 6`\n\n- `(0, 3)`: `nums[0] + nums[3] = 3`\n\n- `(0, 4)`: `nums[0] + nums[4] = 9`\n\n- `(1, 3)`: `nums[1] + nums[3] = 5`\n\n- `(1, 4)`: `nums[1] + nums[4] = 11`\n\n- `(2, 4)`: `nums[2] + nums[4] = 13`\n\nThus, the answer is 13.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [5,1,9], k = 1\n\n**Output:** 14\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Since `k = 1`, every pair is valid.\n\n- The maximum value is obtained from a pair `(0, 2)`, which is `nums[0] + nums[2] = 5 + 9 = 14`.\n\n- Thus, the answer is 14.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= n == nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `1 <= k <= n - 1`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-valid-pair-sum/","problemName":"Maximum Valid Pair Sum","problemNumber":3979,"problemSlug":"maximum-valid-pair-sum","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":3979,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["String","Greedy"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given two [binary strings](leetcode-keyword) `s1` and `s2` of the same length `n`.\n\nYou can perform the following operations on `s1` any number of times, in any order:\n\n- Choose an index `i` such that `s1[i] == '0'`, and change it to `'1'`.\n\n- Choose an index `i` such that `0 <= i < n - 1`, and both `